When you use the Greenhopper feature of parent/child versions and assign issues to a child version, the issue appears in the Issue Navigator as having both the parent and the child version. At this point this is not a problem. When sorting on the version column, however, the Issue Navigator sorts apply only to the parent version -- within the parent version, all issues appear unsorted, with child versions all intermixed, even if the child versions are properly ordered on the Manage Versions page.
